Ing C Olivetti EC SpA &lt;OLIV.M> does notexclude the possibility of investing in a semiconductor venturecurrently under discussion between Italy's &lt;STET - SocietaFinanziaria Telefonica P.A.> and France's Thomson-CSF&lt;TCSF.PA>, an Olivetti spokesman said.    He said that if Olivetti were approached by the twopartners involved and the financial conditions of any proposalwere considered interesting, the company did not exclude thepossibility of investing in the venture. However, Olivetti hadmade no decision on any such investment and did not have at itsdisposal information to evaluate such a move.     Stet and Thomson said last Thursday they were negotiatingan accord involving their respective subsidiaries &lt;SGSMicroelettronica SpA> and &lt;Thomson Semiconducteurs> in thecivil semiconductor field.    They said the accord, once concluded, would be put forapproval to the French and Italian authorities.    The Olivetti spokesman was responding to a Reuters queryabout Italian press reports today saying that Olivetti mightparticipate in the venture with a two pct stake. REUTER&#3;